Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Liang,

It's not a small overhead, as need double memory usage, for common case.
as about other.
OSC prepare a pages to send, each page is fragment. agree ?

OSC don't count an size to send after offset, but count a pages to send over wire (avoid questions - why don't send continues region as single fragment) so in case don't aligned DIO (buffered io always page aligned), we have first fragment with offset != 0, and size != page size, other fragments in transfer is page size, except a last page where we can send less page size.

from other point - OSC able to send full pages in that case, but set a worked offset in own descriptor.

struct niobuf_local {
        __u64           lnb_file_offset;
        __u32           lnb_page_offset;
        __u32           lnb_len;
        __u32           lnb_flags;
        struct page     *lnb_page;
        void            *lnb_data;
        int             lnb_rc;
};

so OSC, OST always know which offset+len used on that page.

single problem in that area - we need reset a UPTODATE page flag on OST to ability to re-read to cache. But again - it's not a problem for a transport layer.
